  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Breakfast is buffet style with lots to choose from like croissants, fresh bread, fruit, jams, cheeses and cold cuts. They try to use zero kilometre local products where possible. It's all served in the breakfast room between 7.30am and 10am. </p>
<p><strong>The Restaurant</strong> is exclusively for hotel guests and takes inspiration from traditional Neapolitan cuisine. If you're staying on half board you'll have a five-course dinner here each evening. The chefs serve up creative dishes that highlight the amazing local produce and flavours. The wine cellar is well stocked with a great choice of regional wines. </p>
<p><strong>Al Ristoro del Moro</strong> is the hotel's à la carte restaurant that serves local cuisine using fresh produce that can be enjoyed on the lovely sea view terrace. We recommend making a reservation to ensure you get the best seats in the house. </p>
<p><strong>American Bar</strong> offers a comfortable space for a drink. Sit back in the lounge on one of the large sofas and admire views of the sea and the carefully thought-out furnishings and wall art.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
